<p><img src="data:image/jpeg;base64,"></p><p><strong>Adding keywords allows you to input words/phrases that associates would likely use to search for the newly added video.</strong></p><p>1. Access the database.</p><p>a. Go to <a href="mediacenter.plastipak.com/phpMyAdmin" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);"><strong><u>mediacenter.plastipak.com/phpMyAdmin</u></strong></a> (may require VPN connection).</p><p>b. Click the <strong>+</strong> sign next to database name, then click <strong>Search</strong>, copy and paste the video name, select <strong>search_videos</strong> from the drop down box and click <strong>Go</strong>.</p><p>c. When the results appear, click on <strong>Browse</strong>. Verify it is the correct video and click on the pencil to Edit.</p><p>d. In the keyword field, add keywords separated by a comma. Do not include spaces between commas and the next keyword. </p><ul><li>Example: locations,sites,worldwide locations,global sites,includeme</li><li>Use the phrase <strong>includeme</strong> as a keyword to enable the video to be pulled up with the keyword search.</li></ul><p>e. There is no need to run the script again. Go back to <a href="mediacenter.plastipak.com" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);"><strong><u>mediacenter.plastipak.com</u></strong></a> and refresh the browser.</p>
